      <section eId="sec_7_1_240">
        <num>7-1-240</num>
        <content>
          <p>Any financial institution authorized by law to act as both a bank and a trust company shall enjoy and be subject to the powers and restrictions of a bank of its type in regard to its banking activities and in like manner shall enjoy and be subject to the powers and restrictions of a trust company in regard to its trust activity. With respect to general corporate matters not identified with either banking or trust functions, it shall have the privileges and restrictions of a bank of its type.</p>
          <p>(Code 1933, ยง 41A-1101, enacted by Ga. L. 1974, p. 705, ยง 1.)</p>
